[1]
Date: 28 Sep 2004
From: Laurence Gleeson <Laurence.Gleeson@csiro.au>

A confirmation of type C will be a very interesting epidemiological event.
At a global level, it has been a number of years since an outbreak of
serotype C has been reported. So, the question will arise as to where this
virus has been hiding for this length of time, and what the closest
sequence is in the current type C data bank.
--
Laurence Gleeson
Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation
CSIRO Australia
<Laurence.Gleeson@csiro.au>
<http://csiro.au/>
